Welcome to the W3C Media & Entertainment Interest Group!

You can find more information about our group, including charter, participants list, and publications, here:

https://www.w3.org/groups/ig/me

There's a short video introduction to our group:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cYNO34vZyw4

There are links to all our previous meeting minutes on our wiki:

https://www.w3.org/2011/webtv/wiki/Main_Page

We use GitHub to capture issues and topics to discuss in the group:

https://github.com/w3c/media-and-entertainment

We have a monthly teleconference, on the first Tuesday of each month. Depending on your location, the time may vary due to daylight savings changes. 

- 07:00 (US Pacific), 15:00 (UK), 16:00 (Central Europe)
- November to March: 22:00pm (China), 23:00 (Korea and Japan) 
- April to October: 23:00pm (China), 00:00 (Wednesday, Korea and Japan)

You can find the connection details here:

https://lists.w3.org/Archives/Member/member-web-and-tv/2018Sep/0001.html

If you have any questions, or if there are any topics you would like to bring to the group, please feel free to contact us.

We look forward to your participation.

Kind regards,

The Media & Entertainment Interest Group co-chairs:

Tatsuya Igarashi (Tatsuya.Igarashi@sony.com)
Pierre-Anthony Lemieux (pal@sandflow.com)
Chris Needham (chris.needham@bbc.co.uk)
